  "original_title": "\u0d95\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ambassador of Oman meets President",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Oman's Ambassador Ahmed Ali Saeed Al Rashidi has told the President that the two countries will help strengthen bilateral ties on fuel, gas, energy, employment and investment opportunities.",
        "The Omani ambassador, who is to leave the island after finishing his service, mentioned this while meeting President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa at the Fort President's House in Colombo today (01).",
        "About 25,000 Sri Lankans are currently working in Oman. The President also asked the Ambassador to assist in increasing job opportunities in the training sector.",
        "The president appreciated the support provided to Sri Lanka during the 08 years of service of Mr. Syed Al Rashd and discussed the wide scope for trade and investment opportunities in the country.",
        "Mr. Rashd mentioned with the President that he is proposed to report to the service of the Omani Foreign Ministry and work to strengthen the relations between the two countries from there."
      ],
